": 7}], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Whitleya tangutica are iridoid glycosides, including whitleyoside and tangutinoside, which have shown anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, while other constituents include phenolic acids and flavonoids, which may contribute to its antimicrobial and cardiovascular protective effects. Iridoid glycosides have been found to exert anti-inflammatory effects through the inhibition of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, and also possess antioxidant properties by scavenging free radicals and enhancing glutathione levels. Phenolic acids, specifically gallic acid, have been reported to exhibit antimicrobial activity against various pathogens, including bacteria and fungi, and to have anti-cancer properties. Flavonoids, including quercetin and kaempferol, have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, as well as cardiovascular protective effects through the modulation of endothelial function and lipid profiles. Additionally, the flavonoid quercetin has been reported to have anti-cancer properties by inhibiting cell proliferation and inducing apoptosis in cancer cells.", "herb_names_common": [{"name": "whitleya tangutica", "mentions": 25, "confidence_score": 151, "total_score": 3775}, {"name": "whitlaya tangutica", "mentions": 13, "confidence_score": 96, "total_score": 1248}, {"name": "whitleya", "mentions": 16, "confidence_score": 89, "total_score": 1424}, {"name": "whitelaya", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 37, "total_score": 296}, {"name": "chinese lovage", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 112}, {"name": "tangutian sage", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 27, "total_score": 540}, {"name": "tangut lovage", "mentions": 3, "confidence_score": 26, "total_score": 78}, {"name": "whitelaya tangutica", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 22, "total_score": 88}, {"name": "chinese whitleya", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 22, "total_score": 8